## CMB map

## Creation of an unlensed cosmic microwave background

map_extension = 120             # size of the squared map in arcmin
resolution = 0.2                # size of the pixels in arcmin
n = map_extension/resolution    # number of pixels

background = map_maker(map_size=map_extension, pixel_size=resolution, pixel_number=n, l_degrees=6000)

background.load_and_make_spectrum("/home/user/Physik_Bonn/research_project/resources/TT_power_spectrum_extended_planck18cosmo.dat")
background_map_fs, background_map, background_map_real = background.make_gaussian_random_field(zero_dipole=False, spectrum_type = "acoustic")
background.plot_gaussian_random_field()
print("RMS = " + str(background.rms_estimation()))

## Lens

## Creation of a lensing map containing the deflection angle at each map position.
## The deflaction angle is computed using its relation to the convergence.
## An NFW-galaxy cluster is assumed as the lens object.

lens = nfw_lens()

lens.make_map(map_extension, resolution)
lens.kappa()
lens.kappa2alpha()

alpha1 = np.array([lens.alphaX, lens.alphaY])

## plot map of deflection angles
im_alpha1 = plt.imshow(np.sqrt(lens.alphaX**2 + lens.alphaY**2), extent=[0, map_extension, 0, map_extension], origin='lower', interpolation='bilinear', cmap='RdBu')
im_alpha1.set_clim()

plt.xlabel(r"$\theta_x$[arcmin]")
plt.ylabel(r"$\theta_y$[arcmin]")

cbar = plt.colorbar(im_alpha1)
cbar.set_label(r"$|\alpha|$ [arcmin]")   # label for the scale

## lensed map
## Creation of the lensed CMB map by applying the lensing map (using convergence)

output1 = lensing(pre_lens_map=background_map_real, lens = alpha1)
output1.lensing_map = alpha1

output1.copy_map_parameters()
output1._make_pos_map()

output1.apply_lensing()


im_diff1 = plt.imshow(output1.get_lensed_map()-background_map_real, extent=[0, map_extension, 0, map_extension], origin='lower', interpolation='bilinear', cmap='RdBu')
im_diff1.set_clim()

plt.xlabel(r"$\theta_x$[arcmin]")
plt.ylabel(r"$\theta_y$[arcmin]")

cbar = plt.colorbar(im_diff1)
cbar.set_label("T [K]")   # label for the scale

Map parameters: map_size = 600, pixel_size = 1, pixel_number = 600.

output2 = lensing(pre_lens_map=background_map_real, lens = alpha2)
output2.lensing_map = alpha2

output2.copy_map_parameters()
output2._make_pos_map()

output2.apply_lensing()

diff = output2.get_lensed_map()-background_map_real
#np.max(abs(diff))
threshold = np.max(abs(diff))/10  # values above this will be set to zero

above_values = diff[abs(diff) > threshold]

diff[abs(diff) > threshold] = threshold

im_diff2 = plt.imshow(diff, extent=[0, map_extension, 0, map_extension], origin='lower', interpolation='bilinear', cmap='RdBu')
im_diff2.set_clim()

plt.xlabel(r"$\theta_x$[arcmin]")
plt.ylabel(r"$\theta_y$[arcmin]")

cbar = plt.colorbar(im_diff2)
cbar.set_label("T [K]")   # label for the scale
